.TH EXIFAUTOTRAN "1" "February 2005" "exifautotran" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
exifautotran \- Transforms Exif files so that Orientation becomes 1
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B exifautotran
.I jpegfile
[\fIjpegfile\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
exifautotran [list of files]
.PP
Take a list of files as input and transform them in place so that the
Orientation becomes 1.
.PP
The packaged wrapper resolves
.BR jpegtran (1)
and
.BR jpegexiforient (1)
relative to its own installed location so that the staged safe binaries are
used consistently.
.PP
The authoritative packaged wrapper source remains
.BR safe/debian/extra/exifautotran ,
paired with this committed manpage and the Rust
.B jpegexiforient
helper under
.BR safe/crates/jpeg-tools/src/bin .
.PP
The committed wrapper and manpage are staged from
.B safe/debian/extra
without consulting the upstream tree at package-build time.
.SH "AUTHOR"
    Guido Vollbeding <guido@jpegclub.org>
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR jpegtran(1)
.BR jpegexiforient(1)
